Title : Pearse Peninsula
Text : The '''Pearse Peninsula''' is a [[peninsula]] on the southwest end of [[Broughton Island (British Columbia)|Broughton Island]] in the [[Broughton Archipelago]] of the [[Queen Charlotte Strait]] region of the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast of British Columbia]], [[Canada]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/26466.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Pearse Peninsula"]</ref>

==Name origin==
The peninsula was named in 1860 for Commander [[William Alfred Rumbulow Pearse]], [[Royal Navy|RN]], who commanded [[HMS Alert (1856)|HMS ''Alert'']] in the area from 1858-1861.  He is also the namesake of the [[Pearse Islands]] at the northern entrance to the [[Johnstone Strait]].<ref>''British Columbia Coast Names, 1592-1906: their origin and history'', Captain John T. Walbran, Ottawa, 1909, quoted in BC Names"</ref>

